CNCP v1 23267
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#14031: `after-enter` event triggered even when `transition` wrapped in `keep-alive` never shows its child",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:15:55.199187+00:00",
  "text": "`after-enter` event triggered even when `transition` wrapped in `keep-alive` never shows its child\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.22\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nClick the button repeatedly, and you’ll notice that `after-enter` is logged in the console.\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe `after-enter` event should not be triggered when no transition is applied.\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nThe `after-enter` event is triggered even when the element wrapped in a `transition` is never displayed.\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n[discussion #14030](https://github.com/orgs/vuejs/discussions/14030)",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
